  - abstract: The strong coupling dynamics of string theories in dimension d ⩾ 4 are
      studied. It is argued, among other things, that eleven-dimensional
      supergravity arises as a low energy limit of the ten-dimensional Type IIA
      superstring, and that a recently conjectured duality between the heterotic
      string and Type IIA superstrings controls the strong coupling dynamics of
      the heterotic string in five, six, and seven dimensions and implies
      S-duality for both heterotic and Type II strings.
