  - abstract: Preface. Abel's name is associated with a number of key notions of
      modern mathematics, such as abelian varieties, Abel's integrals, etc.
      Moreover, it became almost synonymous with the idea of commutativity.
      Thus, when one speaks about abelian class field theory, one has in mind a
      description of extensions of a ground (say, number) field with commutative
      Galois group.
