    title: The Hopf fibration—seven times in physics
    url: https://doi.org/10.1016/S0393-0440(02)00121-3
    date-published: 2003-01-01
    year: 2003
    issn: 0393-0440
    issue: "2"
    journal: Journal of Geometry and Physics
    start: "125"
    end: "150"
    type: article
    volume: "46"
  - abstract: We discuss a generalization of the standard Bloch sphere
      representation for a single qubit to two qubits, in the framework of Hopf
      fibrations of high-dimensional spheres by lower dimensional spheres. The
      single-qubit Hilbert space is the three-dimensional sphere S 3. The S 2
      base space of a suitably oriented S 3 Hopf fibration is nothing but the
      Bloch sphere, while the circular fibres represent the overall qubit phase
      degree of freedom. For the two-qubits case, the Hilbert space is a
      seven-dimensional sphere S 7, which also allows for a Hopf fibration, with
      S 3 fibres and a S 4 base. The most striking result is that suitably
      oriented S 7 Hopf fibrations are entanglement sensitive. The relation with
      the standard Schmidt decomposition is also discussed.
    authors:
      - family-names: Mosseri
        given-names: Rémy
      - family-names: Dandoloff
        given-names: Rossen
